\begin_layout Standard
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 be a 2d matrix complex matrix:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
A=\left(\begin{array}{cc}
a_{1,1} & a_{1,2}\\
a_{2,1} & a_{2,2}
\end{array}\right)
\]

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order do investigate spectral properties of matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 we should consider corresponding characteristic equation:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
det\left(A-\lambda E\right)=0
\]

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

 is unitary matrix.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let us solve this equation...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $det\left(A-\lambda E\right)=0$
\end_inset

,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $det\left(\begin{array}{cc}
\left\{ a_{1,1}-\lambda\right\}  & a_{1,2}\\
a_{2,1} & \left\{ a_{2,2}-\lambda\right\} 
\end{array}\right)=0$
\end_inset

,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\left(a_{1,1}-\lambda\right)\left(a_{2,2}-\lambda\right)-a_{1,2}a_{2,1}=0$
\end_inset

,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda^{2}-\lambda(a_{1,1}+a_{2,2})+a_{1,1}a_{2,2}-a_{1,2}a_{2,1}=0$
\end_inset

,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda^{2}-\lambda\cdot tr(A)+det(A)=0$
\end_inset

,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus one can easily get two eigenvalues of 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda_{1,2}=\frac{tr(A)\pm\sqrt{D}}{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
with discriminant 
